Ille genis color eniteat, quo mixta corallis Marmora, vel quali candida poma rubent. Caesaries auro rutilet: debetur ocellis, Qualis inest gemmis sideribusque, nitor. Forma supercilii sit, qualem Cypridis arcus, Vel Triviae, leviter cum sinuatur, habet. Sed pictor suspende manum ; subtilius omni Stamine, quod tentas hic simulare, vides. Cedit Apollineo vulsus de vertice crinis, Cedit Apellea linea ducta manu. Pinge supercilium sine fastu, pinge pudicos Huic oculos, totam da sine labe Deam. Ut careat naevo formae nil deme vel adde, Fae similem tantum, qua potes arte, sui.

Cambessa] Daughter os Archibald, seventh Earl oi Argyll, the carl who had such a strange history (see CXIV. 8). She married George, Earl ol Enzie and Lord Aboyne, asterwards second Marquis oi Huntly. This marchioness died 14th June, 1638, and was buried at St. Machar's, Aherdeen.
